<section id="fs-id1477528" class="free-response">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-id1536012">
<problem id="fs-id3077000"><para id="fs-id2178087">Describe how metabolism can be altered.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1610652"><label/>
<para id="fs-id2936218">An increase or decrease in lean muscle mass will result in an increase or decrease in metabolism.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id2165558">
<problem id="fs-id1362015"><para id="fs-id2189036">Describe how Addison’s disease can be treated.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2040569"><label/>
<para id="fs-id1363996">Addison’s disease is characterized by low cortisol levels. One way to treat the disease is by giving cortisol to the patient.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
